<sect1 id="zend.date.overview">

    <title>Zend_Date API Overview</title>

    <para>
        While the <code>Zend_Date</code> API remains simplistic and unitary it is very rich and mighty.
    </para>

    <para>
        The following overview should provide help to the functions.
    </para>

    <sect2 id="zend.date.overview.general">

        <title>General Functions</title>

        <para>
            The general functions expect a constant providing the date's desired part (such as Zend_Date::HOUR). Those
            constants are valid to all functions. A list of all available constants is provided in
            <xref linkend="zend.date.constants" />
        </para>

        <para>
            The following general functions will be available:
        </para>

        <table>
            <title>General functions</title>
            <tgroup cols="2">
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry>Function</entry>
                        <entry>Description</entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <link linkend="zend.date.output.get">get()</link>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>date output</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <link linkend="zend.date.setting.set">set()</link>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>setting a new date</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <link linkend="zend.date.maths.add">add()</link>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>adding with dates</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <link linkend="zend.date.maths.sub">sub()</link>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>subtraction with dates</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>copy()</entry>
                        <entry>copy a date and return a new object</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <link linkend="zend.date.maths.compare">compare()</link>
